# HTTP Monitor Request Configuration (MON-HTTP-01)

Full spec: [docs/MONITOR-HTTP-REQUESTS.md](../../docs/MONITOR-HTTP-REQUESTS.md)

## Config storage

All HTTP/keyword/ssl advanced settings live in `monitors.config` (JSONB). Do not add new DB columns.

## Single request mode

When `config.steps` is empty, use top-level fields:

- `method`, `body`, `headers`, `expectedStatus`, `keyword`, `timeout`

## Request chain mode

When `config.steps` is non-empty:

- Execute steps sequentially (max 5)
- Step 1 URL defaults to monitor `targetUrl` if blank
- Substitute `{{varName}}` in url/body/headers from prior extracts
- Extract via `json` (dot path), `regex` (capture group 1), or `header`
- Fail fast on wrong status or extract error

## Code locations

| Layer | Path |
|-------|------|
| Executor | `apps/api/internal/services/http_chain.go` |
| Config types | `apps/api/internal/services/http_config.go` |
| Entry | `RunCheck()` in `checks.go` |
| UI component | `apps/web/src/components/monitor-http-config.tsx` |
| Shared TS types | `apps/web/src/lib/monitor-config.ts` |

## UI rules

- Show HTTP config for types: `http`, `keyword`, `ssl` only
- Toggle "Enable request chain" switches single vs multi-step UI
- Edit page must PATCH `config` alongside name/url/interval
- All strings via next-intl (`monitors.*` keys)

## After changes

Follow **Mandatory post-change workflow** in `.cursor/rules/pulsewatch.mdc` (test → commit → deploy → verify → push).

For this feature specifically:

1. `go test ./internal/services/...` in `apps/api`
2. `cd deploy && node redeploy-api.js` + `node redeploy-web.js`
3. Browser-verify `/monitors/new` and `/monitors/[id]/edit`
